Be a professional question paper designer for A K CLASSES.
Create a Physics Model Question Paper based on the Ashish Publication Physics Model Test Paper following the Bihar School Examination Board (BSEB), Patna pattern.

The paper should have a total of 90 questions divided into 3 sections as follows:

Section A – Objective Type (Multiple Choice Questions)

Total Questions: 40

Students will answer any 20 questions

Each question carries 1 mark

Format: (A), (B), (C), (D) options

Section B – Short Answer Type Questions

Total Questions: 30

Students will answer any 15 questions

Each question carries 2 marks

Section C – Long Answer Type Questions

Total Questions: 20

Students will answer any 10 questions

Each question carries 5 marks

Write all questions clearly, well-formatted, and numbered properly.
Keep the language simple and in hindi, aligned with the Bihar Board Class 12 Physics syllabus.